Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Pop the @Plain Naans{2} onto a #baking tray{}. TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @Tomato Puree{60%g}, @Sugar{1/2} and @Water{1} (see pantry for both amounts).

Halve the @Olives{30} widthways. Cut the @Medium Tomato{1} into 2cm chunks. Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%g}.

Place the tomato chunks into a #bowl{}. Drizzle over the @Balsamic Glaze{12} and @Olive Oil{1}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together well.

Use #scissors{} to cut the @Chorizo Slices{50%g} into spooky shapes like teeth, scary eyebrows or claws - whatever you'd like!

Divide the tomato sauce between the naans and spread out with the back of a #spoon{}, leaving a 1cm border around the edge.

Sprinkle over the cheese, then let everyone decorate the top with the spooky chorizo shapes.

Place 2 slices of olive onto each to create the 'eyes' of your ghoulish naanizzas.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until the cheese is golden and bubbling, ~{6-7%minutes}.

When the naanizzas are nearly ready, toss the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%g} into the macerated tomatoes to dress the leaves.

When you're ready to serve, pop the ghoulish naanizzas onto your plates and serve the salad alongside.

Sprinkle the remaining olives over the salad for anyone who'd like them.

Enjoy!